## Final Summary

```
IP Address     = Device Identifier
Subnet Mask    = Separates Network and Host Portions
CIDR           = Number of Network Bits
Magic Number   = Finds Subnet Blocks
Network Addr   = First Address in Block
Broadcast Addr = Last Address in Block
Usable Range   = Everything Between Network and Broadcast
VLSM           = Different Subnet Sizes to Reduce Waste
Supernetting   = Combining Networks
Good Design    = No Overlap + Minimal Waste
```
